You're driving.

273
00:14:01.264 --> 00:14:04.230
But we got to make a stop
along the way.

274
00:14:04.297 --> 00:14:05.435
No problem.

275
00:14:05.539 --> 00:14:06.366
Calm down?!

276
00:14:06.401 --> 00:14:07.815
Are you fucking kidding me?!

277
00:14:07.884 --> 00:14:10.229
Yeah. fuck that. Austin Lewis.

278
00:14:10.297 --> 00:14:12.056
I haven't even begun
to lose my shit yet.

279
00:14:12.125 --> 00:14:14.573
Now you let me in to see Wes
right the fuck now!

280
00:14:14.608 --> 00:14:15.918
What the fuck is wrong
with you?!

281
00:14:15.953 --> 00:14:17.194
[Austin]
I haven't seen him in a week.

282
00:14:17.229 --> 00:14:18.229
I promise you. Whit.
he ain't here.

283
00:14:18.297 --> 00:14:19.953
Joaquin will tell you the same.

284
00:14:20.849 --> 00:14:22.366
Miss Ayers.

285
00:14:22.470 --> 00:14:24.263
Whitney.

286
00:14:27.228 --> 00:14:28.814
[chuckles softly]

287
00:14:28.883 --> 00:14:30.228
Back to work. men.

288
00:14:35.434 --> 00:14:36.572
Mm.

289
00:14:38.676 --> 00:14:40.055
Sit a minute?

290
00:14:40.159 --> 00:14:41.883
Sit?

291
00:14:44.745 --> 00:14:45.883
Okay. Come on.

292
00:14:45.917 --> 00:14:47.537
Come on. honey.

293
00:14:49.882 --> 00:14:51.192
All right.

294
00:14:51.261 --> 00:14:53.261
- [babbling]
- [sighs]

295
00:14:53.330 --> 00:14:54.778
[chuckles]

296
00:14:57.606 --> 00:14:59.606
Wes hasn't shown in days.

297
00:15:01.330 --> 00:15:03.020
That's not him.

298
00:15:03.089 --> 00:15:05.502
We hoped he got homesick.

299
00:15:05.606 --> 00:15:06.985
With good reason.

300
00:15:07.054 --> 00:15:09.984
He only gets homesick
for this goddamn bunkhouse.

301
00:15:10.088 --> 00:15:11.226
Where do they say he is?

302
00:15:11.294 --> 00:15:12.398
They don't.

303
00:15:13.226 --> 00:15:15.329
They'd be only rumors
if they did.

304
00:15:16.536 --> 00:15:18.226
Please.

305
00:15:19.329 --> 00:15:20.777
Come on. I need to know.

306
00:15:20.881 --> 00:15:22.570
Maybe a woman.

307
00:15:22.639 --> 00:15:25.053
But it's just rumors.

308
00:15:26.639 --> 00:15:27.812
No.

309
00:15:28.605 --> 00:15:30.397
[sniffles]

310
00:15:30.466 --> 00:15:31.880
Wes ain't no saint.

311
00:15:31.949 --> 00:15:33.914
but this boy changed him.

312
00:15:35.087 --> 00:15:36.776
Ask Austin.

313
00:15:37.949 --> 00:15:39.431
Wes loves being a daddy.

314
00:15:39.466 --> 00:15:40.880
He would never walk out on us.

315
00:15:40.949 --> 00:15:42.328
[sniffles]

316
00:15:46.156 --> 00:15:47.949
I don't fucking buy it.

317
00:15:47.983 --> 00:15:50.225
♪ low. tense music

318
00:15:52.292 --> 00:15:53.465
[sniffles]

319
00:16:07.844 --> 00:16:10.396
Mind if we stop for a piss?

320
00:16:12.361 --> 00:16:15.050
- Almost 100 miles of silence.
- Don't know

321
00:16:15.154 --> 00:16:16.257
if you've ever been locked up.

322
00:16:16.326 --> 00:16:17.843
but I can tell you
a bit of silence

323
00:16:17.912 --> 00:16:20.085
is the best sound I've heard
in an awful long time.

324
00:16:28.429 --> 00:16:29.705
[door closes]

325
00:16:31.395 --> 00:16:33.567
♪ low. tense music ♪

326
00:16:40.946 --> 00:16:43.497
[Beulah] <i>Chet. did you know
that this ranch dates back</i>

327
00:16:43.532 --> 00:16:45.015
<i>to before the Alamo fell?</i>

328
00:16:45.084 --> 00:16:46.497
Yes. ma'am.

329
00:16:46.566 --> 00:16:49.325
That longhorn there descended
from our very first.

330
00:16:50.153 --> 00:16:53.463
Stolen in 1836
by an Irish Catholic immigrant.

331
00:16:53.532 --> 00:16:54.773
[chuckles softly]

332
00:16:54.842 --> 00:16:56.703
His grit built this legacy.

333
00:16:56.738 --> 00:16:59.014
And I've worked very hard
to protect it.

334
00:16:59.083 --> 00:16:59.979
Yes. ma'am.

335
00:17:00.014 --> 00:17:01.462
I want to believe

336
00:17:01.531 --> 00:17:03.565
you're the man
to help me uphold that legacy.

337
00:17:03.634 --> 00:17:05.462
to safeguard it. Are you?

338
00:17:05.531 --> 00:17:06.427
I am.

339
00:17:06.531 --> 00:17:08.565
I mean. I can.

340
00:17:08.669 --> 00:17:09.945
I will.

341
00:17:11.014 --> 00:17:12.117
Good.

342
00:17:12.186 --> 00:17:13.945
- [sips drink]
- [sets glass down]

343
00:17:17.702 --> 00:17:20.978
Start by reinstating
law and order in the bunkhouse.

344
00:17:21.047 --> 00:17:22.944
No more questions.
no more bullshit.

345
00:17:23.013 --> 00:17:24.909
I will not tolerate
disappointment.

346
00:17:25.013 --> 00:17:26.082
Just ask my son.

347
00:17:26.185 --> 00:17:28.220
I won't let you down.

348
00:17:31.461 --> 00:17:32.978
You were there.

349
00:17:36.013 --> 00:17:37.254
Ma'am?

350
00:17:37.323 --> 00:17:39.012
With Rob-Will...

351
00:17:39.081 --> 00:17:40.563
that night.

352
00:17:40.598 --> 00:17:42.770
♪

353
00:17:46.667 --> 00:17:49.391
Now we understand each other.

354
00:17:50.287 --> 00:17:51.391
Yes. ma'am.

355
00:17:51.494 --> 00:17:52.736
Good.

356
00:17:53.874 --> 00:17:55.115
You may go.

357
00:17:59.012 --> 00:18:01.218
♪

358
00:18:06.355 --> 00:18:08.493
[loud mooing]

359
00:18:20.631 --> 00:18:22.148
It's not the ride they mind.

360
00:18:22.182 --> 00:18:23.803
It's the speed.

361
00:18:24.665 --> 00:18:27.182
Slow and steady.

362
00:18:27.251 --> 00:18:29.113
We'll be just fine.

363
00:18:29.148 --> 00:18:30.975
I'm going under 70.

364
00:18:31.010 --> 00:18:33.320
Yeah. you don't strike me
as the slow lane type.

365
00:18:33.389 --> 00:18:35.320
Well. never used to be.

366
00:18:35.423 --> 00:18:36.975
Yeah. And now?

367
00:18:41.492 --> 00:18:42.974
All right.

368
00:18:43.043 --> 00:18:45.216
[decelerating]

369
00:18:49.147 --> 00:18:50.284
- Gummy worm?
- I'm good.

370
00:18:50.319 --> 00:18:52.147
- Thank you.
- [chuckling]

371
00:18:52.181 --> 00:18:53.526
Okay.

372
00:18:58.629 --> 00:19:00.767
Seawolves?

373
00:19:02.422 --> 00:19:03.973
A long way from the ocean.

374
00:19:04.042 --> 00:19:05.594
Yeah. we are.

375
00:19:05.697 --> 00:19:10.525
I was a naval aviator for
a helicopter attack squadron.

376
00:19:10.594 --> 00:19:12.215
Mekong Delta.

377
00:19:13.146 --> 00:19:15.421
Don't worry. I won't ask.

378
00:19:15.490 --> 00:19:17.490
Well. I don't mind if you ask.

379
00:19:17.559 --> 00:19:18.421
Just not...

380
00:19:18.525 --> 00:19:19.594
not that much to say.

381
00:19:19.663 --> 00:19:21.766
I was young and...

382
00:19:22.559 --> 00:19:24.421
...looking for someone to save.

383
00:19:24.525 --> 00:19:25.903
something to fight.

384
00:19:25.972 --> 00:19:27.524
[grunts]

385
00:19:27.593 --> 00:19:29.800
It was a long time ago.

386
00:19:29.869 --> 00:19:32.524
I bet you got medals.

387
00:19:32.627 --> 00:19:34.455
A few.

388
00:19:34.524 --> 00:19:35.765
What for?

389
00:19:35.834 --> 00:19:37.041
[chuckles softly]

390
00:19:37.145 --> 00:19:39.351
My abundant stupidity.

391
00:19:39.386 --> 00:19:41.248
You should be proud of them.

392
00:19:41.317 --> 00:19:42.593
Well...

393
00:19:43.869 --> 00:19:46.523
You should never take
that hat off.

394
00:19:47.350 --> 00:19:49.075
Only at the dinner table.

395
00:19:54.213 --> 00:19:55.764
<i>♪ Yeah. my guitars ♪</i>

396
00:19:55.833 --> 00:19:57.385
<i>♪ Cadillacs ♪</i>

397
00:19:57.454 --> 00:19:59.730
<i>♪ Hillbilly music ♪</i>

398
00:19:59.764 --> 00:20:04.523
<i>♪ The only thing
that keeps me hanging on ♪</i>

399
00:20:05.592 --> 00:20:07.799
♪ low. somber music

400
00:20:11.349 --> 00:20:14.246
You bought the Edwards Ranch?

401
00:20:14.315 --> 00:20:15.384
We did.

402
00:20:16.246 --> 00:20:18.143
There's a cot there
in that hay barn.

403
00:20:18.212 --> 00:20:19.384
It ain't much.

404
00:20:19.487 --> 00:20:21.212
but it'll do.

405
00:20:21.246 --> 00:20:22.970
Thank you. sir.

406
00:20:28.763 --> 00:20:29.831
Don't get too comfortable.

407
00:20:29.900 --> 00:20:31.383
We got shit to do today.

408
00:20:31.452 --> 00:20:32.659
Yes. sir.

409
00:20:42.107 --> 00:20:44.762
[birds singing]

410
00:20:55.520 --> 00:20:57.278
Shit. you got old.

411
00:20:58.175 --> 00:21:00.347
You got tall.

412
00:21:06.141 --> 00:21:08.210
Good to see you. boy.

413
00:21:11.520 --> 00:21:13.553
However you did this...

414
00:21:14.415 --> 00:21:15.588
...thank you.

415
00:21:17.829 --> 00:21:19.519
[in Spanish]
Your horse for the day.

416
00:21:24.346 --> 00:21:25.346
Hey.

417
00:21:25.450 --> 00:21:27.105
Rip don't suffer fools.

418
00:21:27.174 --> 00:21:29.657
Okay? Just be ready.
be fast. be good.

419
00:21:29.760 --> 00:21:31.071
You'll be just fine.

420
00:21:31.312 --> 00:21:32.622
[in Spanish]
Thanks Azul.

421
00:21:32.967 --> 00:21:34.035
You can count on me.

422
00:21:34.104 --> 00:21:35.621
Shit. you speak Spanish.
too. huh?

423
00:21:35.656 --> 00:21:36.690
South Texas. sir.

424
00:21:36.759 --> 00:21:38.104
Fish or cut bait.

425
00:21:38.139 --> 00:21:39.311
[chuckles]

426
00:21:40.104 --> 00:21:42.725
Well. how...
how do you say "mount up"?

427
00:21:42.794 --> 00:21:44.070
<i>- Móntense.</i>
- Well.

428
00:21:44.139 --> 00:21:45.656
fucking <i>móntense.</i>

429
00:21:45.759 --> 00:21:47.932
We're gonna get those
open heifers out of Black Rock.

430
00:21:48.001 --> 00:21:48.897
push 'em over to Mistress.

431
00:21:48.966 --> 00:21:51.208
We got a new bull coming in.

432
00:21:51.276 --> 00:21:52.208
Let's go to work.

433
00:21:52.276 --> 00:21:54.208
- Yes. sir.
- [smooching]

434
00:21:59.862 --> 00:22:02.103
[soft chatter]

435
00:22:04.448 --> 00:22:05.965
Carter!

436
00:22:06.034 --> 00:22:07.310
[Carter chuckles]

437
00:22:11.448 --> 00:22:12.310
Got your text.

438
00:22:12.379 --> 00:22:13.413
You want to rob a liquor store?

439
00:22:13.517 --> 00:22:15.069
- [sighs] Got algebra.
- Mm.

440
00:22:15.172 --> 00:22:17.309
You'll never use it.

441
00:22:17.378 --> 00:22:18.619
But this?

442
00:22:19.964 --> 00:22:21.068
Mm.

443
00:22:21.137 --> 00:22:22.585
It'll solve
all kind of problems.

444
00:22:22.654 --> 00:22:23.964
Come on.

445
00:22:24.033 --> 00:22:25.895
- All right.
- Ah.

446
00:22:27.102 --> 00:22:28.343
[Oreana exhales]

447
00:22:28.378 --> 00:22:29.723
Buckle up.

448
00:22:30.585 --> 00:22:31.585
[engine starts]

449
00:22:31.654 --> 00:22:34.688
♪ low. mysterious music ♪

450
00:22:34.723 --> 00:22:37.240
[engine revving]

451
00:22:37.343 --> 00:22:39.411
[shouting]

452
00:22:39.515 --> 00:22:41.205
[whistling]

453
00:22:41.480 --> 00:22:43.342
♪

454
00:22:45.377 --> 00:22:47.549
[clanging]

455
00:22:50.825 --> 00:22:53.032
♪

456
00:22:55.860 --> 00:22:56.963
[bellows]

457
00:22:58.342 --> 00:22:59.617
Ha!
[whistles]

458
00:23:01.204 --> 00:23:02.721
- [whistles]
- [grunts]

459
00:23:02.790 --> 00:23:05.790
Get the fuck out of my way. boy.

460
00:23:05.893 --> 00:23:07.928
- [snorting]
- Don't know

461
00:23:07.962 --> 00:23:10.341
who's more upset that Wes
ran off. you or his wife.

462
00:23:10.410 --> 00:23:11.479
Fucking let it go.

463
00:23:11.583 --> 00:23:13.031
Problem is. you won't let it go.

464
00:23:13.100 --> 00:23:14.410
Stirring up trouble
for all of us.

465
00:23:14.479 --> 00:23:15.928
You know damn well
that Wes didn't run off.

466
00:23:15.997 --> 00:23:17.376
[man shouting]

467
00:23:17.445 --> 00:23:18.997
Getting real sick
of your shit today.

468
00:23:19.066 --> 00:23:20.892
Hey! Knock it off!

469
00:23:21.547 --> 00:23:24.099
- Shut your mouth. motherfucker.
- Or what?

470
00:23:24.168 --> 00:23:26.065
♪ tense. suspenseful music ♪

471
00:23:30.754 --> 00:23:32.513
- [Chet] Hey!
- Ah!

472
00:23:32.582 --> 00:23:34.099
That wasn't
a fucking suggestion.

473
00:23:34.134 --> 00:23:36.823
- Ah!
- It was a goddamn commandment.

474
00:23:44.477 --> 00:23:45.822
You got fight. boy.

475
00:23:45.926 --> 00:23:47.788
I'll give you that.

476
00:23:47.822 --> 00:23:49.753
But zero fucking sense.

477
00:23:49.822 --> 00:23:51.133
Ah!

478
00:23:53.167 --> 00:23:55.615
I guess I got to beat some
into you. huh?

479
00:23:55.719 --> 00:23:57.546
[shouts]

480
00:23:57.615 --> 00:23:59.133
[Austin coughing]

481
00:23:59.236 --> 00:24:00.788
Get these two tended.

482
00:24:00.857 --> 00:24:03.442
If they ain't dead. I want them
on a horse in an hour.

483
00:24:03.511 --> 00:24:05.166
Yes. sir.

484
00:24:05.201 --> 00:24:07.269
♪

485
00:24:08.166 --> 00:24:09.925
[bell jingles]

486
00:24:11.132 --> 00:24:13.304
[in Spanish]
You're fine. Felipe.

487
00:24:13.959 --> 00:24:15.545
She doesn't bite.

488
00:24:16.235 --> 00:24:17.890
Claudio. My friend Beth.

489
00:24:17.959 --> 00:24:19.545
[Beth] Thank you
for seeing us. Claudio.

490
00:24:19.649 --> 00:24:23.476
Everett tells me that you cut
the finest T-bone in the state.

491
00:24:23.545 --> 00:24:26.303
- [Claudio] I do.
- Well. I got six Angus outside

492
00:24:26.372 --> 00:24:27.820
with nowhere to take them.

493
00:24:27.889 --> 00:24:29.889
My husband and I.
we're building a small outfit.

494
00:24:31.165 --> 00:24:33.027
Quality. family-run.

495
00:24:33.096 --> 00:24:34.613
Like you.

496
00:24:34.682 --> 00:24:36.924
- [giggles]
- Ooh.

497
00:24:37.717 --> 00:24:40.855
He's gonna be climbing the
fucking walls tonight. Everett.

498
00:24:42.751 --> 00:24:44.303
Let me show you what I do.

499
00:24:44.372 --> 00:24:46.543
♪ slow. gentle music ♪

500
00:24:48.130 --> 00:24:49.957
We're a four-man operation.

501
00:24:50.026 --> 00:24:53.199
but I'll stake our work
against the big boys any day.

502
00:24:57.267 --> 00:24:59.819
I'm gonna need the best cuts
to hook the best buyers.

503
00:24:59.854 --> 00:25:01.888
Prime grade. certified Angus.

504
00:25:01.957 --> 00:25:03.302
[Claudio]
How old are your steers?

505
00:25:03.371 --> 00:25:04.681
- [Beth] Around 22 months.
- [Claudio] Good.

506
00:25:04.750 --> 00:25:06.819
[Beth] We'll lead with rib eye.
filet. T-bone.

507
00:25:06.888 --> 00:25:09.508
- Peak marbling.
- You know what you want.

508
00:25:09.577 --> 00:25:11.646
- It's what I need.
- Charge you market rates.

509
00:25:11.715 --> 00:25:13.129
all on the level.

510
00:25:13.198 --> 00:25:14.956
Thank you.

511
00:25:15.749 --> 00:25:18.025
- How long?
- Three weeks.

512
00:25:18.094 --> 00:25:19.956
How's two?

513
00:25:22.335 --> 00:25:25.508
[cattle lowing]

514
00:25:28.370 --> 00:25:30.472
♪

515
00:25:32.748 --> 00:25:34.886
Hey! Hey!

516
00:25:40.645 --> 00:25:41.645
Yo.

517
00:25:41.714 --> 00:25:43.472
Whoa.

518
00:25:46.128 --> 00:25:47.610
Shh-shh. Hey!

519
00:25:49.748 --> 00:25:51.161
[grunting]

520
00:25:51.230 --> 00:25:52.920
Oh. oh.

521
00:25:52.954 --> 00:25:54.747
Oh!

522
00:26:03.678 --> 00:26:05.782
Jailbird. you're still a cowboy.

523
00:26:05.851 --> 00:26:08.471
[chuckles]
Hell yeah.

524
00:26:08.575 --> 00:26:10.402
Feels good.

525
00:26:10.471 --> 00:26:13.850
♪ inspiring string music ♪

526
00:26:17.091 --> 00:26:18.677
[gunshot]

527
00:26:20.677 --> 00:26:22.298
Hmm?

528
00:26:22.332 --> 00:26:23.850
You good with it?

529
00:26:23.953 --> 00:26:26.022
I can work one okay.

530
00:26:26.815 --> 00:26:28.436
Fire away.

531
00:26:30.815 --> 00:26:32.470
[exhales sharply]

532
00:26:33.504 --> 00:26:35.021
[gunshots]

533
00:26:39.987 --> 00:26:41.297
You fucking with me?

534
00:26:41.331 --> 00:26:42.918
Maybe just a little.

535
00:26:42.987 --> 00:26:44.676
I like that.

536
00:26:45.918 --> 00:26:47.056
Hmm.

537
00:26:47.125 --> 00:26:49.504
♪ serene music ♪

538
00:26:55.986 --> 00:26:57.813
Your daddy teach you
how to shoot?

539
00:26:57.917 --> 00:26:59.813
Uh. no.

540
00:27:00.606 --> 00:27:03.606
One of the other cowboys
on our old ranch.

541
00:27:04.503 --> 00:27:06.744
[laughs softly]

542
00:27:06.848 --> 00:27:09.710
Now. you're a mystery. Carter.

543
00:27:11.055 --> 00:27:14.227
Kind of handsome. kind of not.

544
00:27:14.330 --> 00:27:17.743
- [scoffs]
- Parking lot hero.

545
00:27:17.847 --> 00:27:19.985
crack shot.

546
00:27:22.916 --> 00:27:25.226
What else you hiding
behind them eyes?

547
00:27:30.536 --> 00:27:32.433
[chuckles]

548
00:27:32.536 --> 00:27:34.881
Look. I'm sorry
I got you. uh. mixed up

549
00:27:34.950 --> 00:27:37.087
in all my drama at the rodeo.

550
00:27:37.915 --> 00:27:39.294
Um...

551
00:27:39.363 --> 00:27:42.466
I'm just glad to get mixed up
in something.

552
00:27:42.535 --> 00:27:44.880
♪ gentle music ♪

553
00:27:44.915 --> 00:27:47.604
You know. nobody's gonna
make it easy for you. Carter.

554
00:27:48.397 --> 00:27:49.673
You've got to do that yourself.

555
00:27:49.742 --> 00:27:51.777
You just got to say. "Fuck it."

556
00:27:52.570 --> 00:27:54.191
"Fuck all of them."

557
00:27:56.225 --> 00:27:58.465
Do whatever the fuck you want.

558
00:28:04.879 --> 00:28:05.983
[sighs]

559
00:28:06.879 --> 00:28:08.431
[chuckles]

560
00:28:19.809 --> 00:28:22.464
♪

561
00:28:23.326 --> 00:28:25.326
[footsteps approaching]

562
00:28:25.395 --> 00:28:26.982
<i>Jefa.</i>

563
00:28:27.085 --> 00:28:28.844
Rob-Will's checked into rehab.

564
00:28:28.913 --> 00:28:30.395
The one in Sedona?

565
00:28:30.464 --> 00:28:32.809
Yeah. five-star accommodations.
like you asked.

566
00:28:32.878 --> 00:28:34.637
Does my father know about this?

567
00:28:34.740 --> 00:28:37.223
The day-to-day operations
of our business

568
00:28:37.292 --> 00:28:38.533
are not his concern.

569
00:28:38.602 --> 00:28:40.878
The ranch is my dominion.
not his.

570
00:28:42.774 --> 00:28:46.188
Cleaning up Rob-Will's mess
is proving to be difficult.

571
00:28:47.912 --> 00:28:49.291
Well. in what way?

572
00:28:49.325 --> 00:28:53.188
In the way it got up and walked
off the Edwards Ranch.

573
00:28:54.843 --> 00:28:56.946
Well. you'd better
fucking find it.

574
00:28:57.050 --> 00:28:59.946
This is my brother's fault.
not mine.

575
00:29:00.015 --> 00:29:02.394
One day he's gonna set a fire
I cannot contain.

576
00:29:02.497 --> 00:29:04.393
Well. it wouldn't be a problem
if you hadn't let

577
00:29:04.497 --> 00:29:07.118
that property slip
through our fingers.

578
00:29:07.187 --> 00:29:08.876
The Edwards never liked us.

579
00:29:09.738 --> 00:29:11.324
Sold the ranch
to that Montana couple.

580
00:29:11.359 --> 00:29:12.945
The late governor's daughter.

581
00:29:13.014 --> 00:29:14.462
We met.

582
00:29:14.531 --> 00:29:16.945
She came by the slaughterhouse.

583
00:29:17.014 --> 00:29:17.876
For what?

584
00:29:17.980 --> 00:29:20.738
To kill and carve her cows.

585
00:29:20.807 --> 00:29:22.221
or that's what she told me.

586
00:29:22.324 --> 00:29:24.186
You need to find out
what they know

587
00:29:24.254 --> 00:29:26.186
before it gets more complicated.

588
00:29:29.358 --> 00:29:30.875
Ah. your new foreman

589
00:29:30.910 --> 00:29:33.496
already put a hand
in the hospital.

590
00:29:33.599 --> 00:29:34.806
Austin.

591
00:29:34.875 --> 00:29:35.737
Hmm.

592
00:29:35.806 --> 00:29:37.358
How bad off is he?

593
00:29:37.427 --> 00:29:39.151
Broken arm. broken ribs.

594
00:29:39.186 --> 00:29:41.806
[sighs]
What. was he asking questions?

595
00:29:41.841 --> 00:29:44.530
Wes's wife paid him a visit.

596
00:29:44.599 --> 00:29:46.150
She was asking questions. too.

597
00:29:46.219 --> 00:29:47.529
Well. then go do
something about it

598
00:29:47.598 --> 00:29:50.081
before this becomes
a fucking wildfire.

599
00:29:54.495 --> 00:29:55.598
[sighs]

600
00:29:55.667 --> 00:29:57.150
[indistinct chatter
in background]

601
00:29:57.185 --> 00:29:59.116
[indistinct radio transmission]

602
00:29:59.185 --> 00:30:01.357
I need to file
a missing persons report.

603
00:30:01.460 --> 00:30:02.633
Go ahead and take a seat.

604
00:30:02.702 --> 00:30:04.357
No. I don't have time
to take a seat.

605
00:30:04.391 --> 00:30:06.357
Ma'am. just take a seat.

606
00:30:06.426 --> 00:30:08.528
- Someone will be right with you.
- My husband is missing. okay?

607
00:30:08.632 --> 00:30:10.046
And I got my little boy

608
00:30:10.080 --> 00:30:12.356
at a friend's trailer who starts
her shift in a half hour

609
00:30:12.390 --> 00:30:14.908
and I got to get back to him.
so can you please just take

610
00:30:15.011 --> 00:30:17.184
- my goddamn information?
- Can I help you?

611
00:30:17.287 --> 00:30:18.873
Be nice if somebody did.

612
00:30:18.908 --> 00:30:21.666
I'm Sheriff Wade.
What seems to be the problem?

613
00:30:21.770 --> 00:30:23.459
My husband Wes Ayers.

614
00:30:23.528 --> 00:30:25.356
Works at the 10-Petal Ranch.

615
00:30:25.425 --> 00:30:27.046
Disappeared from the bunkhouse.

616
00:30:27.149 --> 00:30:29.183
Went to bed.
didn't wake up there.

617
00:30:29.286 --> 00:30:30.665
Never came home.

618
00:30:32.010 --> 00:30:33.665
Would you step into my office?

619
00:30:38.700 --> 00:30:41.010
Now. how long has he been gone?

620
00:30:41.045 --> 00:30:42.769
Long enough to know
something's wrong.

621
00:30:42.838 --> 00:30:44.389
Did anybody see him take off?

622
00:30:44.458 --> 00:30:45.941
Well. no one who's talking.

623
00:30:46.010 --> 00:30:47.562
I mean. they said
maybe he took off.

624
00:30:47.631 --> 00:30:49.492
needed some space.
[scoffs]

625
00:30:49.561 --> 00:30:50.975
And who said that?
Was that the foreman?

626
00:30:51.009 --> 00:30:52.837
Ranch owner's son.
[scoffs]

627
00:30:52.906 --> 00:30:54.664
Tried saying maybe
he was off the wagon.

628
00:30:54.699 --> 00:30:56.182
but it ain't fucking true.

629
00:30:56.250 --> 00:30:58.733
- And you're sure about that?
- Wes doesn't need space.

630
00:30:58.802 --> 00:31:00.216
He needs a paycheck
and a shower.

631
00:31:00.319 --> 00:31:01.630
Ma'am. I understand that.
but sometimes grown--

632
00:31:01.733 --> 00:31:02.940
Are you gonna help me
or judge me?

633
00:31:03.009 --> 00:31:05.906
Yes. Ms. Ayers.
we are gonna help you.

634
00:31:05.975 --> 00:31:08.044
But there is a process to this.

635
00:31:08.113 --> 00:31:11.353
We will take your information
after it's been 72 hours.

636
00:31:11.422 --> 00:31:13.249
It's been 72 hours.

637
00:31:14.077 --> 00:31:18.249
Someone at the 10-Petal
knows more than they're saying.

638
00:31:18.353 --> 00:31:20.560
♪ slow. dark music ♪

639
00:31:22.560 --> 00:31:24.077
That's a pretty serious
accusation.

640
00:31:24.181 --> 00:31:26.767
Yeah. well. so is
disappearing a man.

641
00:31:27.560 --> 00:31:29.525
How do I know someone
won't come for me next?

642
00:31:29.560 --> 00:31:31.146
[sniffles]

643
00:31:34.180 --> 00:31:35.938
It's gonna be all right.

644
00:31:36.007 --> 00:31:37.662
Start the report.

645
00:31:39.145 --> 00:31:41.180
We'll take care of it for you.
all right?

646
00:31:41.248 --> 00:31:42.904
Call me if you need anything.

647
00:31:42.973 --> 00:31:44.559
Thank you.

648
00:31:45.869 --> 00:31:47.076
All right. what do you need?

649
00:31:47.180 --> 00:31:49.248
[deputy] Spell
your husband's name for me.

650
00:31:53.523 --> 00:31:54.592
That's good!

651
00:31:54.627 --> 00:31:57.385
- [bellowing]
- [metal thudding]

652
00:31:58.972 --> 00:32:01.144
Zachariah.
when we open this second gate.

653
00:32:01.247 --> 00:32:02.282
I want you to clear out.

654
00:32:02.316 --> 00:32:03.834
Don't got to tell me twice.

655
00:32:03.937 --> 00:32:06.454
- Get this son of a bitch--
- Don't fucking use that.

656
00:32:06.558 --> 00:32:08.247
Dipshit.

657
00:32:08.316 --> 00:32:10.075
♪ tense music ♪

658
00:32:10.144 --> 00:32:11.420
I really don't got the time.

659
00:32:11.489 --> 00:32:14.420
[bellowing]

660
00:32:36.763 --> 00:32:39.177
Go earn your keep.

661
00:32:40.487 --> 00:32:43.280
♪ hopeful music ♪

662
00:32:43.314 --> 00:32:44.728
It's right there.

663
00:32:50.383 --> 00:32:52.521
[both chuckle]

664
00:32:53.797 --> 00:32:55.314
So. uh...

665
00:32:56.108 --> 00:32:57.969
...when do you think
I could see you again?

666
00:32:58.072 --> 00:32:59.555
[phone chiming]

667
00:33:04.003 --> 00:33:06.210
♪ dramatic guitar music ♪

668
00:33:08.210 --> 00:33:12.038
I have a boyfriend. Carter.

669
00:33:30.968 --> 00:33:32.071
[sighs]

670
00:33:41.070 --> 00:33:42.967
Happy to do that. sir.

671
00:33:43.036 --> 00:33:44.691
[Rip]
All right.

672
00:33:49.311 --> 00:33:50.656
Azul.

673
00:33:51.898 --> 00:33:53.691
Thank you. sir.

674
00:33:54.587 --> 00:33:55.656
[in Spanish]
All good?

675
00:33:56.484 --> 00:33:57.656
Yeah. thanks.

676
00:33:57.725 --> 00:33:59.380
[Azul]
My old man would've been happy

677
00:33:59.415 --> 00:34:00.932
to see you like this.

678
00:34:01.001 --> 00:34:02.897
[Zach]
You know. after what happened.

679
00:34:02.966 --> 00:34:05.448
seemed like the whole world
turned against me.

680
00:34:05.483 --> 00:34:07.379
But not Hector.

681
00:34:09.104 --> 00:34:11.276
He never looked at me
any different.

682
00:34:11.310 --> 00:34:13.104
♪ slow. dramatic music

683
00:34:13.173 --> 00:34:15.276
You know. he'd visit.

684
00:34:15.345 --> 00:34:17.379
Third Sunday.

685
00:34:17.448 --> 00:34:18.828
Nearly every month.

686
00:34:19.621 --> 00:34:22.173
He never said it. but I knew.

687
00:34:26.034 --> 00:34:28.172
[in Spanish]
Your dad was a gift.

688
00:34:28.689 --> 00:34:30.172
A gift from God.

689
00:34:31.758 --> 00:34:33.137
<i>Sí.</i>

690
00:34:33.999 --> 00:34:35.482
A gift from God.

691
00:34:35.827 --> 00:34:37.999
♪

692
00:34:41.792 --> 00:34:43.896
- [footsteps approaching]
- [Beulah sighs]

693
00:34:43.965 --> 00:34:45.033
Oh.

694
00:34:45.102 --> 00:34:47.067
Perfect timing. Dinner's ready.

695
00:34:47.136 --> 00:34:49.929
I already drank mine. Thanks.

696
00:34:50.757 --> 00:34:54.550
So. Suzanne Norris says you had
quite a night at the rodeo.

697
00:34:54.619 --> 00:34:57.308
- [chuckles] I sure did.
- Mm-hmm.

698
00:34:57.412 --> 00:35:02.205
Some steer wrestler put
his hands on my granddaughter.

699
00:35:03.033 --> 00:35:04.239
How does that look?

700
00:35:04.343 --> 00:35:06.273
For Beulah Jackson?

701
00:35:06.342 --> 00:35:09.445
- Heaven forbid.
- Hmm.

702
00:35:09.514 --> 00:35:11.411
Sit down.

703
00:35:11.480 --> 00:35:13.859
- I'll stand.
- Sit down!

704
00:35:13.928 --> 00:35:14.894
Now!

705
00:35:29.858 --> 00:35:31.893
I sent your daddy off to rehab.

706
00:35:31.996 --> 00:35:33.237
So I've been told.

707
00:35:33.306 --> 00:35:35.479
It's past time
he addressed his demons.

708
00:35:35.548 --> 00:35:37.169
Demons that you helped create.

709
00:35:37.203 --> 00:35:38.824
Excuse me?

710
00:35:40.410 --> 00:35:43.169
Oreana Lynn.
you are right on his heels.

711
00:35:43.237 --> 00:35:45.824
and I won't accept it.
I won't tolerate it.

712
00:35:45.893 --> 00:35:48.341
This family cannot survive
another fucked-up child.

713
00:35:48.410 --> 00:35:50.409
You can't survive it.

714
00:35:50.512 --> 00:35:52.581
Just like you can't
survive me being

715
00:35:52.650 --> 00:35:54.685
- anything other than perfect.
- You have to be perfect

716
00:35:54.719 --> 00:35:57.926
if you want to take over
running this ranch.

717
00:35:57.995 --> 00:35:59.857
I pray to God that I don't.

718
00:36:01.443 --> 00:36:03.236
That I never turn into you.

719
00:36:03.305 --> 00:36:05.478
♪ slow. tense music ♪

720
00:36:10.684 --> 00:36:12.856
You grow the fuck up.

721
00:36:13.718 --> 00:36:15.891
Eat your dinner
before it gets cold.

722
00:36:15.925 --> 00:36:18.167
[footsteps receding]

723
00:36:21.339 --> 00:36:22.649
Yes. ma'am.

724
00:36:22.718 --> 00:36:24.994
♪

725
00:36:55.544 --> 00:36:56.785
You find him?

726
00:36:56.820 --> 00:37:00.130
No. No. I was just out
this way. and I--

727
00:37:00.199 --> 00:37:02.096
No one is just out this way.

728
00:37:02.165 --> 00:37:05.751
I wanted to personally bring you
Wes's last two weeks.

729
00:37:05.820 --> 00:37:09.061
and I added his next two weeks.

730
00:37:10.199 --> 00:37:11.578
[paper rustling]

731
00:37:11.647 --> 00:37:14.957
Hmm. That's mighty decent
of you.

732
00:37:15.026 --> 00:37:16.129
It's the least we can do

733
00:37:16.164 --> 00:37:17.853
- for our 10-Petal family.
- Mm-hmm.

734
00:37:18.715 --> 00:37:21.646
Sheriff is being
awfully kind. too.

735
00:37:21.681 --> 00:37:23.267
Paid him a visit today.

736
00:37:23.336 --> 00:37:25.370
♪ slow. tense music ♪

737
00:37:26.681 --> 00:37:29.129
Fuck you and your money.

738
00:37:34.577 --> 00:37:36.714
♪

739
00:37:39.818 --> 00:37:41.335
[vehicle door opens]

740
00:37:41.438 --> 00:37:43.335
[vehicle door closes]

741
00:37:43.369 --> 00:37:45.163
[engine starts]

742
00:37:52.852 --> 00:37:54.680
You want to talk
about something?

743
00:37:54.749 --> 00:37:56.990
No. It's nothing.

744
00:37:58.437 --> 00:38:00.541
[Rip exhales]

745
00:38:00.644 --> 00:38:02.713
Spit it out. Carter.

746
00:38:04.162 --> 00:38:05.920
For fuck's sakes. just tell me.
What's on your mind?

747
00:38:06.024 --> 00:38:08.230
- Come on. man.
- [groans]

748
00:38:09.299 --> 00:38:10.886
I-I met a girl.

749
00:38:11.782 --> 00:38:13.024
Oh. thank God.

750
00:38:13.093 --> 00:38:15.920
I mean. n-no. that.
that's-that's good.

751
00:38:15.989 --> 00:38:18.230
Uh. I'm just not sure
what to do.

752
00:38:18.334 --> 00:38:20.229
Well. you don't do anything.
you don't say anything.

753
00:38:20.264 --> 00:38:22.195
You just listen.
That's the deal.

754
00:38:22.264 --> 00:38:24.712
She says something nice to you.
you listen.

755
00:38:24.747 --> 00:38:26.436
She says something mean
to you. you listen.

756
00:38:26.505 --> 00:38:28.540
And if you don't know what
the fuck she's talking about.

757
00:38:28.574 --> 00:38:29.919
you listen.

758
00:38:31.471 --> 00:38:33.643
- Just listen?
- Yeah.

759
00:38:36.885 --> 00:38:39.402
You know. years ago.

760
00:38:39.505 --> 00:38:42.022
I asked John. I said. um.

761
00:38:42.091 --> 00:38:45.435
"What's the key
to a successful relationship?"

762
00:38:45.539 --> 00:38:47.642
He said.
"The first day. she's right.

763
00:38:47.711 --> 00:38:49.815
The second day.
she's right again.

764
00:38:49.884 --> 00:38:52.401
And the third day.
you're fucking wrong."

765
00:38:52.470 --> 00:38:54.228
[chuckles]

766
00:38:54.332 --> 00:38:55.470
Yeah.

767
00:38:55.539 --> 00:38:57.435
You ever. uh...

768
00:38:58.228 --> 00:39:01.848
...you ever liked a girl
that's with another guy?

769
00:39:05.055 --> 00:39:06.159
Hey.

770
00:39:06.262 --> 00:39:07.400
Sweetheart.

771
00:39:07.469 --> 00:39:09.400
Steak's still warm.

772
00:39:11.848 --> 00:39:13.262
Did I miss all the fun?

773
00:39:18.469 --> 00:39:20.331
So. what are you talking about?

774
00:39:20.400 --> 00:39:22.916
- Just man stuff.
- [chuckles]

775
00:39:23.778 --> 00:39:25.951
By that. you mean girl stuff?

776
00:39:31.330 --> 00:39:32.709
We're back in business.

777
00:39:33.537 --> 00:39:34.364
Good.

778
00:39:34.433 --> 00:39:36.123
And I think I found a bar.

779
00:39:36.192 --> 00:39:37.847
- Oh. yeah?
- Yeah.

780
00:39:37.916 --> 00:39:39.640
There's someone there
waiting to meet you.

781
00:39:39.709 --> 00:39:41.640
- Meet me. huh?
- Yep.

782
00:39:41.744 --> 00:39:43.744
Do you think I could come?

783
00:39:43.778 --> 00:39:46.501
School night. baby.

784
00:39:49.915 --> 00:39:52.019
[chuckles]

785
00:39:52.088 --> 00:39:54.294
♪ atmospheric music ♪

786
00:39:56.260 --> 00:39:59.122
["Heart-Shaped Necklace"
by Cassidy Daniels playing]

787
00:39:59.225 --> 00:40:01.019
<i>♪ In a rain shower ♪</i>

788
00:40:01.088 --> 00:40:05.122
<i>♪ 'Cause he knows me
like the back of his hand ♪</i>

789
00:40:05.191 --> 00:40:06.638
<i>♪ I don't want another... ♪</i>

790
00:40:06.707 --> 00:40:08.259
- Everett.
- Hmm?

791
00:40:08.328 --> 00:40:10.224
- This is my husband Rip.
- Yeah.

792
00:40:10.293 --> 00:40:12.811
Rip. this is Everett.

793
00:40:12.880 --> 00:40:14.431
I'll be right back.

794
00:40:14.466 --> 00:40:16.983
Carol. could you get
a beer for my husband?

795
00:40:17.018 --> 00:40:19.431
- And I'll have a Tito's.
- Yep. You got it.

796
00:40:20.776 --> 00:40:22.293
Thank you.

797
00:40:23.121 --> 00:40:25.569
Well. what do you say. Everett?

798
00:40:26.362 --> 00:40:28.223
Cards on the table. Rip.

799
00:40:28.292 --> 00:40:30.706
I was all for putting
that mare down.

800
00:40:30.775 --> 00:40:33.637
Your wife felt different.

801
00:40:33.672 --> 00:40:34.844
She was damn convincing.

802
00:40:34.913 --> 00:40:37.086
Yeah. well. no shit.
I live with her.

803
00:40:37.120 --> 00:40:39.396
She don't take
the word "no" very easy.

804
00:40:39.465 --> 00:40:41.603
[scoffs] I could fill
a dictionary with words

805
00:40:41.672 --> 00:40:43.189
when it came to my wife.

806
00:40:44.465 --> 00:40:46.327
I think I have
that same dictionary.

807
00:40:46.430 --> 00:40:48.602
Knowing Jeanie
sold y'all that ranch.

808
00:40:48.671 --> 00:40:52.602
I. I reckon we'll discover
we have more in common.

809
00:40:52.671 --> 00:40:55.843
I tended more animals
on that ranch than any other.

810
00:40:55.912 --> 00:40:58.774
I had a mean crush on Jeanie
in high school.

811
00:40:58.843 --> 00:41:00.498
It was not reciprocated.

812
00:41:00.567 --> 00:41:01.878
[chuckles]

813
00:41:01.947 --> 00:41:04.188
Yeah. I did two tours
with Billy.

814
00:41:05.533 --> 00:41:07.947
He was. he was better at war
than me.

815
00:41:08.016 --> 00:41:09.635
They built a beautiful place.

816
00:41:09.670 --> 00:41:11.049
Yeah. they sure did.

817
00:41:11.118 --> 00:41:14.842
<i>♪ Heart-shaped necklace ♪</i>

818
00:41:14.911 --> 00:41:16.532
[cheering and applause]

819
00:41:24.118 --> 00:41:26.704
All right. how about
we get McKinney up here?

820
00:41:27.497 --> 00:41:29.704
[applause]

821
00:41:33.876 --> 00:41:36.220
[Everett exhales]
All right.

822
00:41:37.289 --> 00:41:38.910
[chuckles]

823
00:41:38.979 --> 00:41:41.152
[guitar playing]

824
00:41:48.358 --> 00:41:49.669
Come on. sweetheart.

